before this was (urlView.scheme() == "snmp"), 
(protocol == "SNMPv2c") is effectively the same check ?

The intent here is that if the user omits the protocol, we try to do the right thing.

Protocol: "SNMPv2c"
Destination: 10.0.0.0

Should end up the same as:
Destination: snmp://10.0.0.0

Because redfish isn't super clear on this, so we need to accept any variation to stay compatible.

The reason for the difference I think is that we're now relying more on the normalized url than actually returning a value from this method.
